12. praeconis ad fastidium, ‘till the crier was tired.’ What part the crier played in the chastisement does not appear. The editors say that he had to go on proclaiming the culprit’s offence, but they allege no adequate authority. Porph.’s note is ‘donec . . . praeco cum vellet desinere iuberet.'
